### --- Group Invitations ---
### Requires: auth_token = TEACHER/ADMIN JWT, group_public_id = existing group

### Create invitation (teacher - group owner)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/teacher/groups/{{group_public_id}}/invitations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "maxUses": 10,
  "expiresAt": "2027-12-31T23:59:59"
}

### List invitations for group
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/teacher/groups/{{group_public_id}}/invitations
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### Deactivate invitation by token
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/teacher/groups/{{group_public_id}}/invitations/{{invitation_token}}
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### --- Public endpoints (no auth) ---

### Get public invitation info
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/invitations/{{invitation_token}}

### Register student via invitation
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/invitations/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{invitation_token}}",
  "email": "nowy.uczen@example.com",
  "username": "nowy_uczen",
  "password": "StrongPass123"
}

### After successful registration:
### - response is 201 Created with a message,
### - account status becomes EMAIL_VERIFICATION_PENDING,
### - student must confirm email through /api/v1/auth/email-verification/* before login.

### --- Error scenarios ---

### Create invitation - token expired (gone)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/invitations/expired-token-uuid

### Register - email already taken
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/invitations/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{invitation_token}}",
  "email": "jan@example.com",
  "username": "unique_username_xyz",
  "password": "StrongPass123"
}
